article.headline: Texas-Arlington 57, Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 55
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas (AP) -- Anthony Vereen scored 20 points, including a go-ahead jumper with 4:29 remaining, to lead Texas-Arlington past Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 57-55 on Saturday. The Mavericks (14-4, 4-2 Southland) won despite hitting just one more field goal after Vereen's go-ahead shot because the Islanders were having the same problem, getting just one field goal in the final nine minutes. Kevin Perkins led A&M-Corpus Christi (5-13, 2-3) with 14 points. UTA led 57-52 when the Islanders' Chris Daniels hit a 3-pointer to make it a two-point game with 1:44 remaining. But those would be the last points of the game. A&M-Corpus Christi's Antonio Topps missed a potential game-winning 3-pointer with 4 seconds left. There were eight ties, and the biggest lead for either team was six points for the Mavericks early in the first half.
